1
00:00:12,644 --> 00:00:14,440
I used to roller skate all the time.
过去我总溜旱冰.

2
00:00:14,837 --> 00:00:16,773
I loved it when I was little.Did you?
小时候我就特别喜欢溜旱冰. 你呢?

3
00:00:17,459 --> 00:00:21,294
No.I went straight from my pram to a surfboard.
No. 我下了婴儿车就直接到冲浪板上去了.

4
00:00:21,786 --> 00:00:22,968
I used to live in the ocean.
我过去一直是在海上生活的.

5
00:00:24,438 --> 00:00:25,396
No wheels required.
不需要轮子.

6
00:00:25,831 --> 00:00:28,234
Well,you're the first surfing physicist I've ever met.
Well, 你是我所遇到的第一位会冲浪的物理学家.

7
00:00:30,153 --> 00:00:30,661
Oh,right.
Oh, right.

8
00:00:31,029 --> 00:00:33,506
Dean told you I used to be a physicist,didn't he?
Dean告诉过你我以前是个物理学家,是不是?

9
00:00:33,821 --> 00:00:34,109
Yes.
Yes.

10
00:00:34,574 --> 00:00:35,681
It's an interesting combination.
这真是个有趣的组合.

11
00:00:36,929 --> 00:00:38,086
I like interesting combinations.
我喜欢有趣的组合.

12
00:00:57,782 --> 00:01:02,071
A surfing,bartending physicist is very interesting.
一个会冲浪的, 在酒吧工作的物理学家, 实在很有意思.

13
00:01:03,493 --> 00:01:04,208
Elena told you.
Elena告诉你了.

14
00:01:04,638 --> 00:01:05,032
Elena told me.
Elena告诉我了.

15
00:01:07,176 --> 00:01:09,951
I'm sorry.I didn't mean any harm,Heather.
很抱歉. 我没有任何恶意, Heather.

16
00:01:10,597 --> 00:01:10,971
That's OK.
没关系.

17
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,469
I like a man with a vivid imagination.
我喜欢想象力丰富的人.

18
00:01:14,416 --> 00:01:14,833
That's good.
那太好了.

19
00:01:15,622 --> 00:01:17,256
I like someone with a sense of humor.
我喜欢有幽默感的人.

20
00:01:28,926 --> 00:01:31,026
But why would you tell someone you were a physicist?
但为什么你总是告诉别人你过去是个物理学家呢?

21
00:01:31,545 --> 00:01:33,013
Well,I used to say I was a doctor.
Well, 我过去一直说我是一名医生.

22
00:01:33,418 --> 00:01:33,792
You didn't.
不可能吧!

23
00:01:34,436 --> 00:01:36,314
But people asked me for medical advice.
但人们向我请教医学方面的知识.

